Wizard polish: distance slider, defaults, mobile UX, status bug, table cleanup

Five tightly-related improvements across the coordinator wizard, vendor
status surfaces, and the shopper discovery experience.

1) Discovery — replace distance buttons with a continuous slider
   - `lib/markets/distance-radius.ts` now exposes a min/max/step grid
     with helpers `clampSliderRadiusKm`, `formatDistanceRadiusKm`, and
     `zoomForRadiusKm` for mapping radius → Google Maps zoom level.
   - `components/markets/distance-radius-picker.tsx` rewritten as a
     native `<input type="range">` (full mobile / a11y support) plus an
     "Everywhere" toggle for the no-radius sentinel.
   - The map now stays mounted in `discover-screen.tsx` even when the
     filtered result set is empty; the empty-state copy is overlaid on
     top of the map so the user keeps spatial context while widening
     the radius. The map auto-rezooms via `MapRadiusFraming` whenever
     the slider value changes.

2) Defaults — phone width, Quarter Auction times, baseline table
   - `app/profile/profile-form.tsx` constrains the phone `<Input>` to
     `max-w-[16rem]` so the field is proportional to a phone number.
   - `lib/wizard/wizard-panel-styles.ts` adds DEFAULT_QUARTER_AUCTION_*
     constants and a `defaultMarketTimesForListingType` helper. The
     wizard uses it to default new QA events to 5:00 PM – 8:00 PM
     while standard markets keep their 8:00 AM – 3:00 PM defaults.
     Flipping the listing type also retunes the schedule fields when
     they still match the previous default.
   - Baseline table size was already 6 ft via
     `DEFAULT_LAYOUT_BASELINE_TABLE_LENGTH_FT`; no change needed.

3) Mobile UX — pointer events, responsive workspace, accessible nav
   - `FloorPlanWorkspace` now stacks vertically below `md` and force-
     collapses both sidebars on mobile entry so the canvas claims the
     full width instead of being crushed between two 240 px rails.
   - `FloorPlanSidebar` only sticky-pins on `md+`, otherwise lays out
     naturally above/below the canvas.
   - `VirtualizedLayoutCanvas` migrated from `onMouse{Down,Move}` to
     PointerEvents so taps register on iOS Safari and dragging works
     for both mouse and touch.
   - Booth-planner fixture / booth cell handlers and the painting
     guards moved to PointerEvents.
   - `WizardNav` stacks full-width on mobile so the Proceed CTA is
     never clipped.
   - Address autocomplete dropdown closes on `pointerdown` (not just
     `mousedown`) so taps outside dismiss the list on touch devices.
   - `LayoutZoomSlider` widened with `touch-manipulation` so the thumb
     is a comfortable mobile drag target.

4) Vendor status — terminal "Applications closed — not selected"
   - `apply-button.tsx` now branches before the `pending` rendering
     when the market is no longer accepting applications, surfacing a
     terminal closed state instead of an indefinite "Pending Review".
     `waitlisted` survives closure as the user explicitly requested.
   - `application-status-ui.ts` exposes a `resolveVendorApplicationStatusUi`
     helper and `vendor-applications-list.tsx` uses it so the My
     Applications dashboard reflects the same final state.

5) Booth fee column removal
   - `category-limit-editor.tsx` drops the Booth Fee `<th>` and `<td>`
     since pricing is uniform across categories. The `pricePerBooth`
     field still persists in state for backward compatibility.
